Subject: LM Studio Corpus Prompt Task Frame Routing 012

Description: Diversified LM Studio worker prompt packet for task-frame routing.

@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\LMStudioWorkerTaskCorpus.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SOPTaskManager.sop

& [LMStudioCorpusPrompt:task_frame_routing_012] is a non-mutating SOP worker prompt packet
  + [task_family] is task_frame_routing
  + [prompt_boundary] is prompt-only, no tools, no file reads, no repo mutation, no hidden-state claims
  + [expected_output] is exactly one raw SOP node named InferenceJobResult with seven property lines and no Markdown
  + [validation_required_fields] is task_subject, lane_fit, authority_boundary, evidence_gate, action_gate, outside, next_step
  + [validation_required_terms] is lane_fit, authority_boundary, evidence_gate, outside
  + [validation_forbidden_terms] is launch silently, credentials are safe, repo mutation by worker, integrated
  + [prompt_text] is:
    You are performing a no-tools SOP inference job from this prompt only.
    Do not call tools, inspect files, mutate state, or claim repo authority.
    Codex owns launch, capture, validation, integration, commits, and pushes.

    SOP primer:
    & [Name] is a subject declaration.
    + [field] is a property or inferred field.
    A task frame holds task subject, lane fit, authority boundary, evidence gate, action gate, outside, and next step.

    Task family:
    task_frame_routing tests whether you can classify work into a safe lane without claiming authority.

    Work unit to route:
    "Summarize a small SOP source document and propose two follow-up questions. No file edits are needed."

    Return exactly these eight raw SOP lines and no extra text:
    & [InferenceJobResult] is task-frame routing proposal
      + [task_subject] is ...
      + [lane_fit] is ...
      + [authority_boundary] is ...
      + [evidence_gate] is ...
      + [action_gate] is ...
      + [outside] is ...
      + [next_step] is ...

    Final check before answering:
    Line 1 must start with &.
    Lines 2 through 8 must use exactly this operator form: two spaces, +, space, [field], space, is, space, value.
    Do not replace is with verbs such as includes, separates, reminds, routes, or contains.
    Replace every ... placeholder with specific content; do not output ellipses or placeholder text.
    Use ASCII only; avoid curly quotes, nonbreaking hyphens, and special punctuation.
    Include the literal terms lane_fit, authority_boundary, evidence_gate, and outside at least once.
    Do not claim launch silently, credentials are safe, repo mutation by worker, or integrated.
